Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> command
Rule 1     command -> LOAD VECTOR
Rule 2     command -> SAVE VECTOR
Rule 3     command -> LOAD MODEL
Rule 4     command -> SAVE MODEL
Rule 5     command -> sentiment
Rule 6     sentiment -> POSITIVE
Rule 7     sentiment -> NEGATIVE
Rule 8     sentiment -> NEUTRAL

Terminals, with rules where they appear

LOAD                 : 1 3
MODEL                : 3 4
NEGATIVE             : 7
NEUTRAL              : 8
POSITIVE             : 6
SAVE                 : 2 4
VECTOR               : 1 2
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

command              : 0
sentiment            : 5

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . command
    (1) command -> . LOAD VECTOR
    (2) command -> . SAVE VECTOR
    (3) command -> . LOAD MODEL
    (4) command -> . SAVE MODEL
    (5) command -> . sentiment
    (6) sentiment -> . POSITIVE
    (7) sentiment -> . NEGATIVE
    (8) sentiment -> . NEUTRAL

    LOAD            shift and go to state 2
    SAVE            shift and go to state 3
    POSITIVE        shift and go to state 5
    NEGATIVE        shift and go to state 6
    NEUTRAL         shift and go to state 7

    command                        shift and go to state 1
    sentiment                      shift and go to state 4

state 1

    (0) S' -> command .



state 2

    (1) command -> LOAD . VECTOR
    (3) command -> LOAD . MODEL

    VECTOR          shift and go to state 8
    MODEL           shift and go to state 9


state 3

    (2) command -> SAVE . VECTOR
    (4) command -> SAVE . MODEL

    VECTOR          shift and go to state 10
    MODEL           shift and go to state 11


state 4

    (5) command -> sentiment .

    $end            reduce using rule 5 (command -> sentiment .)


state 5

    (6) sentiment -> POSITIVE .

    $end            reduce using rule 6 (sentiment -> POSITIVE .)


state 6

    (7) sentiment -> NEGATIVE .

    $end            reduce using rule 7 (sentiment -> NEGATIVE .)


state 7

    (8) sentiment -> NEUTRAL .

    $end            reduce using rule 8 (sentiment -> NEUTRAL .)


state 8

    (1) command -> LOAD VECTOR .

    $end            reduce using rule 1 (command -> LOAD VECTOR .)


state 9

    (3) command -> LOAD MODEL .

    $end            reduce using rule 3 (command -> LOAD MODEL .)


state 10

    (2) command -> SAVE VECTOR .

    $end            reduce using rule 2 (command -> SAVE VECTOR .)


state 11

    (4) command -> SAVE MODEL .

    $end            reduce using rule 4 (command -> SAVE MODEL .)

